(18753, 140, '<h1>Legal notice</h1>\n<h2><br />Scope of applicability</h2>\n<p>This is the official website of IntegrART (hereinafter referred to as \"we\" or \"us\"). We maintain this portal for your information and as a means of communication. We naturally treat as confidential any personal data that you provide us when using this website. In this data protection statement we would like to describe how we deal with your data and what security is involved. The rules defined herein relate to the entire Internet website www.steps.ch. We expressly reserve the right to assert more specific rules on other websites of the Migros Community. We reserve the right to change the data protection statement at any time. All changes are binding.</p>\n<h2>Intellectual property rights and other rights</h2>\n<p>We own and operate this portal. All brand names, names, titles, logos, images, designs, texts and other materials used on this website belong to us, a legal entity of the Migros Community or a contractual partner of the Migros Community. No rights (rights of use, intellectual property rights, etc.) are acquired by calling up, downloading or copying the website. The (complete or partial) reproduction, transfer (electronic or with other means), modification, linking or using the portal for public or commercial purposes is prohibited without prior written consent from the Federation of Migros Cooperatives.</p>\n<h2>Exclusion of liability</h2>\n<p>Any liability on our part (including negligence) that arises from access to the elements of the website or its use (and/or arising from an inability to access or use it) is excluded. Our website contains links to websites of third parties. Please take note that we do not operate or monitor these websites. We therefore reject any responsibility for the content or conformance with statutory data protection regulations by the operators of these linked websites.</p>\n<h2>Data transfer via the Internet</h2>\n<p>The transfer of data between you and us is performed via the Internet. Please take note that the Internet is an open network accessible to everyone and is therefore not considered to be a secure environment in principle. Although the individual data packages are generally transferred in encoded formats, this does not apply to the sender and the receiver. Furthermore, data may be transferred to a foreign country and therefore possibly to a country with a lower level of data protection than that assured in Switzerland, even if the sender and the receiver are located in Switzerland. We therefore reject any responsibility and liability for the security of your data during transmission via the Internet to us.</p>\n<h2>Collection and use of information</h2>\n<p>When our website is accessed, various access data (for example, IP address, date and time of access, name of the file called up, etc.) are stored in a log file (a kind of computer work record that is sent to you by the website). No evaluations are performed that are related to personal information. The data are evaluated anonymously for statistical purposes (for example, to determine how many times the website is accessed per day). The data are treated strictly confidentially and not made accessible outside the Migros Community or to other third parties, unless required under applicable law and specifically by the responsible prosecutorial authorities.</p>\n<h2>Cookies</h2>\n<p>When our website is called up, your computer stores a small data file (\"cookie\"). This technology is used primarily for the precise collection of visitor figures (\"visits\"). In no case does this involve observation or storage of the conduct of individual visitors.</p>\n<h2>Data security</h2>\n<p>Secure storage of your personal data is guaranteed.</p>', '2019-02-21 17:50:27'),
(18754, 142, '<p><strong>Maria Tembe</strong> wurde in Maputo, Mosambik, geboren und absolvierte ihre Ausbildung in zeitgen&ouml;ssischem Tanz im Rahmen des Projekts (In)Dependence von CulturArte, einer Initiative zur Entwicklung zeitgen&ouml;ssischer darstellender Kunst in Maputo. Im Rahmen dieser Ausbildung arbeitete sie mit Choreografen wie Panaibra Gabriel Canda, Martial Chazalon, Martin Champaut, Boyzie Cekwana und Carlos Pez. Daraufhin trat sie als T&auml;nzerin in verschiedenen Produktionen auf, so in <em>(in)dependence</em> (2007) und <em>Borderlines</em> (2010) von Panaibra Gabriel Canda sowie in <em>Inkomati (des)accord</em> (2009) von Panaibra Gabriel Canda und Boyzie Cekwana. Mit diesen Produktionen war sie in Maputo, La Reunion, am HAU in Berlin sowie beim Global Dance Fest, New Mexico, eingeladen. In der Schweiz war sie 2015 im Rahmen von IntegrART mit <em>Borderlines</em> zu Gast.</p>\n<p><strong>Konzept</strong>: Panaibra Gabriel Canda <strong>K&uuml;nstlerische Mitarbeit, Performance</strong>: Maria Tembe <strong>Licht</strong>: Caldino Jose <strong>K&uuml;nstlerische Assistenz</strong>: Vasco Mirine <strong>Musik</strong>: Strange Fruit von Billie Holiday, Rape Me von Kurt Cobain, Ave Maria von Bobby McFerrin <strong>Produktion</strong>: Panaibra Gabriel Canda / CulturArte</p>', '2019-02-12 06:37:30'),
(18755, 157, '<p><strong>Maria Tembe</strong> wurde in Maputo, Mosambik, geboren und absolvierte ihre Ausbildung in zeitgen&ouml;ssischem Tanz im Rahmen des Projekts (In)Dependence von CulturArte, einer Initiative zur Entwicklung zeitgen&ouml;ssischer darstellender Kunst in Maputo. Im Rahmen dieser Ausbildung arbeitete sie mit Choreografen wie Panaibra Gabriel Canda, Martial Chazalon, Martin Champaut, Boyzie Cekwana und Carlos Pez. Daraufhin trat sie als T&auml;nzerin in verschiedenen Produktionen auf, so in <em>(in)dependence</em> (2007) und <em>Borderlines</em> (2010) von Panaibra Gabriel Canda sowie in <em>Inkomati (des)accord</em> (2009) von Panaibra Gabriel Canda und Boyzie Cekwana. Mit diesen Produktionen war sie in Maputo, La Reunion, am HAU in Berlin sowie beim Global Dance Fest, New Mexico, eingeladen. In der Schweiz war sie 2015 im Rahmen von IntegrART mit <em>Borderlines</em> zu Gast.</p>\n<p><strong>Konzept</strong>: Panaibra Gabriel Canda <strong>K&uuml;nstlerische Mitarbeit, Performance</strong>: Maria Tembe <strong>Licht</strong>: Caldino Jose <strong>K&uuml;nstlerische Assistenz</strong>: Vasco Mirine <strong>Musik</strong>: Strange Fruit von Billie Holiday, Rape Me von Kurt Cobain, Ave Maria von Bobby McFerrin <strong>Produktion</strong>: Panaibra Gabriel Canda / CulturArte</p>', '2019-02-12 19:20:54'),
(18756, 158, '<p><strong>Maria Tembe </strong>was born in Maputo, Mozambique and obtained her training in contemporary dance as part of the project (In)Dependence at CulturArte, an initiative that supports temporary performing arts in Maputo. During this training she worked with choreographers such as Panaibra Canda, Martial Chazalon, Martin Champaut, Boyzie Cekwana and Carlos Pez. Following this, she performed as a dancer in various productions, such as <em>(in)dependence</em> (2007) and <em>Borderlines</em> (2010) by Panaibra Canda as well as <em>Inkomati (des)accord</em> (2009) by Panaibra Canda and Boyzie Cekwana. With these productions she was invited to perform at Maputo, La Re?union, HAU in Berlin and the Global DanceFest, New Mexico. In Switzerland she performed <em>Borderlines</em> within the context of IntegrART 2015.</p>\n<p><strong>Concept</strong>: Panaibra Gabriel Canda <strong>Artistic cooperation, performance</strong>: Maria Tembe <strong>Lights</strong>: Caldino Jose <strong>Artistic assistant</strong>: Vasco Mirine Music: &lsquo;Strange Fruit&rsquo; by Billie Holiday, &lsquo;Rape Me&rsquo; by Kurt Cobain, &lsquo;Ave Maria&rsquo; by Bobby Macferrin <strong>Production</strong>: Panaibra Gabriel Canda / CulturArte</p>', '2019-02-12 20:31:32'),
(18757, 160, '<p><strong>Maria Tembe </strong>was born in Maputo, Mozambique and obtained her training in contemporary dance as part of the project (In)Dependence at CulturArte, an initiative that supports temporary performing arts in Maputo. During this training she worked with choreographers such as Panaibra Canda, Martial Chazalon, Martin Champaut, Boyzie Cekwana and Carlos Pez. Following this, she performed as a dancer in various productions, such as <em>(in)dependence</em> (2007) and <em>Borderlines</em> (2010) by Panaibra Canda as well as <em>Inkomati (des)accord</em> (2009) by Panaibra Canda and Boyzie Cekwana. With these productions she was invited to perform at Maputo, La Re?union, HAU in Berlin and the Global DanceFest, New Mexico. In Switzerland she performed <em>Borderlines</em> within the context of IntegrART 2015.</p>\n<p><strong>Concept</strong>: Panaibra Gabriel Canda <strong>Artistic cooperation, performance</strong>: Maria Tembe <strong>Lights</strong>: Caldino Jose <strong>Artistic assistant</strong>: Vasco Mirine Music: &lsquo;Strange Fruit&rsquo; by Billie Holiday, &lsquo;Rape Me&rsquo; by Kurt Cobain, &lsquo;Ave Maria&rsquo; by Bobby Macferrin <strong>Production</strong>: Panaibra Gabriel Canda / CulturArte</p>', '2019-02-12 20:34:09');
